                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270405-174-off960 t18270405-174-victim1014"></join>
                     </persName>
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>EDWARD HULL. I <rs id="t18270405-174-viclabel962" type="occupation">deal in pictures</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270405-174-victim1014 t18270405-174-viclabel962"></join>. On the 22d of February, between four and five o'clock, I was in <placeName id="t18270405-174-crimeloc963">Plumbtree-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270405-174-crimeloc963" type="placeName" value="Plumbtree-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270405-174-crimeloc963" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270405-174-off960 t18270405-174-crimeloc963"></join>, and felt something touch my pocket; I saw the prisoner behind me - I still went on, and soon afterwards missed my handkerchief - I turned, and missed the prisoner; a person, who had been with him, passed me at the time; I turned back, and saw the prisoner standing at a shop door - I said I believed he had picked my pocket; the shop-keeper took hold of him; he then took my handkerchief from under his coat, and put it on the counter.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270405-174-person1015">
                  PHILIP 
                  RILEY
               <interp inst="t18270405-174-person1015" type="surname" value="RILEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270405-174-person1015" type="given" value="PHILIP"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270405-174-person1015" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I was sent for, and took the prisoner with the handkerchief, which laid on the counter.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence (written). I picked it up in the street, where I supposed it had been lost or dropped. I have neither father nor mother, and have been dependant on my uncle and aunt.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 14.</p>
               <p>Recommended to Mercy by the Prosecutor and Jury.</p>
